# Environment Variables for Deployment

# JWT Secret - Generate a strong random string for production
# You can generate one with: openssl rand -base64 32
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production

# Upstash Redis (KV) - Optional but recommended for persistent storage
# Get these from your Upstash dashboard or Vercel Integrations
# KV_REST_API_URL=https://your-store.upstash.io
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=your-kv-token
# KV_REST_API_READ_ONLY_TOKEN=your-kv-read-only-token
# KV_URL=rediss://default:your-token@your-store.upstash.io:6379
# REDIS_URL=rediss://default:your-token@your-store.upstash.io:6379

# Note: Without Redis, achievements will be stored in memory and reset on each deployment
# To enable persistent storage:
# 1. Create an Upstash Redis database at https://upstash.com
# 2. Copy the REST API URL and token from the Upstash dashboard
# 3. Set the KV_REST_API_URL and KV_REST_API_TOKEN environment variables
